author: DANIEL O'LEARY
title: Seahawks RBs Lynch, Jackson were not drag racing: police
text:
Seahawks RBs Lynch, Jackson were not drag racing: police New York Daily News 15 hrs ago DANIEL O'LEARY Â© Provided by New York Daily News Seahwaks RB Fred Jackson is fine after a minor car accident near the team facility, originally reported as a drag race with Marshawn Lynch, but police say there is "no evidence" of that. - Rick Stewart/Getty Images Police say that there was "no evidence of drag racing" with Marshawn Lynch at the scene of Fred Jackson's accident near the Seahawks' practice facility Tuesday, according to NBC K5-TV in Seattle.
AdChoices Chris Daniels says Renton police maintain that there was "no evidence Marshawn Lynch was at crash scene or involved in any way."
TMZSports.com reported earlier Jackson and Lynch were drag racing following practice, but that report was quickly disputed by CBS' Jason La Confora on Twitter.
FOLLOW THE DAILY NEWS SPORTS ON FACEBOOK. "LIKE" US HERE
While TMZ Sports said the running backs were drag racing on a public street, La Canfora cites sources that say Jackson "misjudged a turn" leaving the team facility at a high rate of speed and hit a stop sign. TMZ said it was unclear if he suffered any injuries, but La Canfora's report said Jackson is "fine."
According to Daniels, Jackson was taken back to the team facility so he could be evaluated by the team's medical staff.
